   <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
      <ol class="- topic/ol ">
         <li class="- topic/li ">Explosive atmospheres can be caused by flammable gases, mists or vapors or by combustible dusts. If there is enough of the substance mixed with air, then only an ignition source is required to cause an explosion.</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Explosive atmospheres that may be found within Space are:<ol class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">Storage vessels/areas that contain dangerous substances</li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">Storage vessels/areas that have contained dangerous substances</li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">Storage of flammable wastes</li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">Deliveries from road tankers such as diesel, liquid oxygen, and flammable substance such as acetylene</li>
            </ol>
         </li>
      </ol>
